    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Having a good range of capabilities on a Board is a critical success factor for sound governance.  To ensure Boards are maximising their collective capability and capacity, Boards should:\n\n - develop a skills matrix that identifies the range of competencies required for the Board\n - map the competencies of Board members to the skills matrix to understand who has what capabilities and where there are gaps at Board level\n - Ensure future Board recruitment considers gaps in the Board skills matrix and ideally seeks to fill them\n - Ensure the individual capacity of each Board member is understood, and the available capacity of each Board member is utilised to the optimal extent\n - Consider replacing Board members with a low capacity to contribute above regular Board meetings',
