    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'One or more individuals with explicit responsibility to drive governance improvements can be highly beneficial for a board, particularly in ensuring that governance remains a priority within the organisation.  Further, appointing people with expertise in governance, compliance, and best practices allows the organisation to leverage their knowledge and experience to drive meaningful improvements. \n\nThe gold standard for this is the appointment of a Governance Committee as recommended in our Template:Governance Policy.  Alternatively, having such responsibility assigned to a specific board member by virtue of including it in their job description can meet the requirement for smaller Boards.\n\nA key means of maintaining a focus on the continuous improvement of your governance practices and board efficiency is to maintain a rhythm of annual GovernApp Board assessments and implementing the recommended actions arising.',
