    action_text:
      'It is a State Government requirement under the Associations Incorporation Reform Act 2012 that Incorporated Associations "keep the financial statements submitted to an annual general meeting of the association for at least 7 years after the date of the annual general meeting." (Division 5, Para 105 (1)).\n\nSimilarly, the ACNC and ASIC require financial records to be retained for a minimum seven years.',
