    text: 'Strongly agree',
    detailed: null,
    score: '0.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '30',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "The Board of Directors of a nonprofit organisation is typically not responsible for the day-to-day implementation of the vision and strategy. \n\nThe primary role of a Board of Directors is to provide governance, set strategic direction, and offer oversight to ensure the organisation is operating in accordance with its mission and goals. \n\nThe day-to-day implementation of the organisation's vision and strategy is typically carried out by the executive leadership and staff, who report to the executive director or CEO.\n\nClear communication and collaboration between the Board and executive leadership are essential for the successful execution of the organisation's mission. Regular updates from the executive leadership to the Board, along with effective reporting mechanisms, help maintain transparency and alignment between the Board's governance role and the operational responsibilities of the staff.",
