    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "There is no right or wrong answer for term limits.  The question of whether it is good practice to impose term limits for board positions depend on various factors.\n\nBoards may impose term limits (perhaps on certain roles within the Board) to promote fresh perspectives, match diversity to the key stakeholder groups, and avoid the concentration of power in long standing members.  \n\nBoards may not impose term limits in order to retain long-term organisational knowledge, maintain access to kety Board members' networks, or simply because recruiting new Board volunteers is too difficult.\n\nSee our Model Practice for more details.",
    created_at: '2024-09-10 21:49:50',
