    action_text:
      'Having your Christian ethos documented in various sources, or being under development as an explicit statement of faith, is commendable.  A written statement of faith is an important guiding document for staff, volunteers, and stakeholders which should reflect the foundational values and theological principles that shape your mission and activities.  Standard 1.2 requires that "The organisation must have a written statement of faith... which is consistent with, and is not in conflict with, the Nicene Creed.\n\nStandard 1.2 does allow for the alternative of the organisation being able to "otherwise satisfactorily demonstrate its [faith] commitment", and your ability to draw on various documents that together may comprise a statement of faith may be considered satisfactory.  However, a discreet, written statement of faith is the most objective method of meeting this standard, and we recommend you develop such a statement as the most direct means of meeting this standard.',
