    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'The CMA Standards Council is the final arbiter of whether evidence of your faith basis is sufficient in the absence of an explicit faith statement.\n\nThe ideal solution is to develop a faith statement for your organisation that aligns with the Nicene Creed.  However, if there are reasons why this is not the preferred approach, it may be beneficial to touch base with CMA Standards Council and seek early feedback on the sufficiency of your alternative evidence.',
