    id: '736',
    question_id: '182',
    order: '1',
    text: "I'm not sure if our ministry's charitable purpose is well understood by most of the Board.",
    detailed: null,
    score: '2.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '30',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "ACNC Governance Standard 5 requires that Board members \"act honestly and fairly in the best interests of the charity and for its charitable purposes\".  It is critical for Board members to be really clear on that charitable purpose if they are to fulfil this requirement.\n\nTo ensure charitable purpose is well understood, the induction training for new Board members should ensure that they are provided with a copy of the organisation's constitution (or other founding document).  The induction should include time with the Chair and the CEO to gain further insight into the mission, history, and culture of the organisation.\n\nThe Board should include a review and discussion on it's charitable purpose at a future Board meeting to ensure all members are well versed in the organisation's core purpose.",
    created_at: '2025-01-13 03:42:33',
