      'ACNC Governance Standard 5 requires that Responsible Persons "ensure that the financial affairs of the charity are managed responsibly".  Financial reports provided at 6 to 12 monthly intervals lack the frequency required to allow early intervention where financial issues are emergent.  Board members should be proactively receiving regular financial reports, at least quarterly.  \n\nResponsible People should be able to read, understand and ask questions on these reports.  Note, the responsibility for financial oversight by a Board is joint, and may not be delegated to an individual such as Treasurer or Chief Finance Officer.  Hence, all Board members should familiarise themselves with how to read financial reports.\n\nSpecific reports the Board should be seeing are the profit & loss statement for the period and the balance sheet.\n\nAdditional reports, depending on circumstances, may include:\n\n - Budget variance report\n - Cashflow report\n - Program delivery financial report\n - Major projects financial report\n - Capital expenditure report\n\nThe Victorian Government has developed a template financial policies and procedures manual which, despite having been developed for small business, provides a helpful starting place for either the development of, or a review and improvement of, your organisation\'s financial practices if required.',
