    action_text:
      'ACNC Governance Standard 5 requires that Responsible Persons "ensure that the financial affairs of the charity are managed responsibly".  Board members should convene as the Board on regular occasions, such as monthly, every two months or every quarter.  Board meetings should include a review of the organisation\'s financial status as a standing agenda item.  \n\nSpecific reports the Board should review include as a minimum: \n\n - Profit & loss statement for the period\n - Balance sheet\n\nAdditional reports, depending on circumstances, may include:\n\n - Budget variance report\n - Cashflow report\n - Program delivery financial report\n - Major projects financial report\n - Capital expenditure report\n\nResponsible People should be able to read, understand and ask questions on these reports.  Note, the responsibility for financial oversight by a Board is joint, and may not be delegated to an individual such as  Treasurer or Chief Finance Officer.  Hence, all Board members should familiarise themselves with how to read financial reports.',
