    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'ACNC Governance Standard 5 requires that Responsible Persons "ensure that the financial affairs of the charity are managed responsibly".  The ability of Board members to interpret and interrogate financial reports is a part of this responsibility.\n\nResponsible People should be able to read, understand and ask questions on these reports.  Note, the responsibility for financial oversight by a Board is joint, and all Board members should familiarise themselves with how to read and interrogate financial reports.  \n\nBoard members who are not yet confident with reading financial reports should consider:\n\n - undertaking training in the reading and interpretation of financial reports\n - referring to support materials such as the ACNC resource "Managing charity money: A guide for Responsible People"\n - seeking mentoring support from more experienced Board members\n - co-opting financial expertise onto the Board as advisors to address gaps in Board knowledge and expertise.',
