    score: '2.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '40',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "ACNC Governance Standard 5 requires that Responsible Persons must not allow their organisation to operate while insolvent.\n\nAn organisation is insolvent when it is unable to pay its debts as they fall due. Note that it is of no consequence under law that assets exceed liabilities. The important point is: can\nthe organisation pay its way in carrying on its ministry?\n\nBoards should ensure that a consideration of solvency is part of their review of the organisation's financial status, and that the minutes of Board meetings - which occur with at an ideal minimum of quarterly - include a declaration of solvency.",
