    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '40',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 6.3 requires that "Organisations with an annual revenue of $1 million or more must be audited annually by an appropriately qualified, independent auditor".  Note, this is more stringent obligation than that required by the ACNC for registered charities, which requires charities with revenues of $500k to $2.999m submit their Annual Information Statement and a reviewed or audited  Financial Report within 6 months of the end of your financial year.\n\nThe Board must make urgent arrangements to (if required):\n\n - appoint an appropriately qualified, independent auditor\n - complete any and all overdue audits of Financial reports\n - review audit reports and identify \/ take any corrective actions required\n - submit any and all overdue audited Financial Reports to the ACNC.\n\nNote, registered charities submitting financial reports to the ACNC do not need to additionally submit these reports to ASIC.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 04:21:57',
    updated_at: '2025-01-14 04:21:57',
