      'Standard 6.4 requires that "organisations with an annual revenue of less than $1 million must be reviewed (within the meaning of the Australian Charities and Not-for-profits Act) or audited annually by an appropriately qualified, independent auditor".\n\nNote, this is more stringent obligation than that required by the ACNC for registered charities, which requires only charities with revenues over $500k are required to submit reviewed Financial Reports to the ACNC within 6 months of the end of your financial year.\n\nTo comply with Standard 6.4, the Board must make urgent arrangements to:\n\n - appoint an appropriately qualified, independent audit\n - complete any and all overdue reviews of Financial reports\n - review the(se) review reports and identify \/ take any corrective actions required\n - submit any and all overdue reviewed Financial Reports to the ACNC (only mandatory for charities with revenues over $500k, but optional and recommended as good practice for those under $500k).\n\nNote, registered charities submitting financial reports to the ACNC do not need to additionally submit these reports to ASIC.',
