    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 6.8 requires that the organisation "must not make a loan to staff, volunteers or members of its governing body unless the loan is documented and approved by the governing body".\n\nThe Board should check financial records to see if a loan has ever been made to staff, volunteers or Board members.  If not, no further action is required.  However, if one or more loans are discovered, the Board should investigate the circumstances and nature of the loan(s), whether the loan has been repaid, and if not, when and how repayment is expected.  If the loan is determined to be problematic, the Board should address this in an appropriate manner; this may include requesting immediate repayment; in the event of evidence of fraud, the authorities should be alerted.  The loan should be retrospectively documented and the current Board\'s approval (or otherwise) of the arrangement should be recorded in meeting minutes.  \n\nThe Board should update its financial procedures to ensure any future loans issued to staff, volunteers or Board members are documented and approved by the Board prior to the loan being made.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 04:59:16',
    updated_at: '2025-01-14 04:59:16',
