      'Standard 6.8 requires that if the organisation makes a loan to staff, volunteers or Board members, then the terms of that loan must be "either on arm’s length terms providing a commercial return, or clearly part of an approved remuneration package, or... otherwise within the charitable purposes of the organisation".\n\nThe Board should check financial records to see if a loan has ever been made to staff, volunteers or Board members.  If not, no further action is required.  However, if one or more loans are discovered, the Board should investigate the circumstances to see if it meets the criteria of Standard 6.8. \n\nIf the loan is determined to be problematic, the Board should address this in an appropriate manner; this may include requesting immediate repayment, changing the conditions of the loan, or other appropriate action; in the event of evidence of fraud, the authorities should be alerted.  \n\nThe Board should update its financial procedures to ensure any future loans issued to staff, volunteers or Board members meet these criteria.',
