    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 6.9 requires that "all members of [the audit] committee must be independent and non-executive".  \n\nThe Board should review the status of each Audit committee member to ensure that they satisfy the CMA Standards Council\'s definition of independence, as defined by their Supporting Policy on Governing Body Independence, found at https:\/\/www.cmasc.net.au\/principles-standards\/supporting-policies.\n\nFurther, all members of the the audit committee must be non-executive, meaning that they must not be employed or contracted to work in the organisation.\n\nMembers not satisfying the independent and non-executive criteria must resign from the committee.',
