    action_text:
      'Standard 7.1 requires that "the organisation must... classifies [risks] according to severity and likelihood, and documents appropriate management strategies and insurance programs".  \n\nIn addition to identifying organisation level risks, each risk should be assessed for the severity of the risk to the organisation were it to eventuate, and the likelihood (probability) that it will occur.  Our template Risk Management Policy and Procedure provides guidance on how to do this.  Further, our risk documentation template will automatically determine the overall risk level for all risks based on factoring the  severity and likelihood.\n\nRisks that have an overall risk rating of high or extreme must have mitigation strategies developed that, when implemented, reduce the overall risk level to moderate or better.',
