    score: '3.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'A key contributor to Standard 7.2 is having a whistleblower policy in place.  A whistleblower policy can assist be providing a confidential means by which staff can raise concerns about illegal, unethical, fraudulent or other concerning behaviours that may otherwise be hidden from senior management or the Board.  \n\nIt is a requirement for every NFP that is either a public company limited by guarantee, or has revenue over $1m, that they must have a Whistleblower Policy.  While NFPs with revenue of less that $1m are exempt from the policy requirement, they are still required to comply with whistleblower protection provisions enshrined in the Corporations Act.  This is best achieved through an appropriate policy.\n\nIf you are unsure if your organisation has a Whistleblower Policy, the Board should conduct an investigation to determine if it exists, and to make the policy publicly available.\n\nIf your organisation does not have a Whistleblower policy, the Board should adopt one with some urgency.  Our Whistleblower Policy Template may assist in this process.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 06:58:31',
    updated_at: '2025-01-14 06:58:31',
