    order: '2',
    text: 'Yes, I think so.',
    detailed: null,
    score: '6.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "Standard 8.2 requires that the \"organisation's annual report contain sufficient detail to enable readers to gain a reasonable overview of the activities, performance and achievements of the organisation\".\n\nThe Board should review the layout and content of its Annual Reports against the following ideal content list, and update the Annual Report template to address any gaps it finds:\n\n - Reaffirmation of the organisation's mission and core values;\n - A description of how activities, programs and projects align with the ministry's goals;\n - Provide a detailed narrative of major activities undertaken during the year;\n - Most significant achievements for the year, with qualitative and quantitative data to support the assertions;\n - Highlight specific programs, campaigns, or initiatives with measurable outcomes (e.g., number of beneficiaries, milestones achieved);\n - Case studies or stories to illustrate impact;\n - Outline the composition of the board and key governance activities;\n - Mention any compliance activities, such as audits, and risk management measures;\n - Summarise financial performance, including income, expenses, and financial position;\n - Include audited financial statements if required;                                                                                                                                    \n - Challenges faced during the year and how they were addressed; and\n - Lessons learned and plans for future improvement.",
    created_at: '2025-01-14 08:11:31',
