    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standards 6.3 and 6.4 (whichever applies) require that requires your financial statements be reviewed or audited.  \n\nThis requirement will have been addressed elsewhere.  Once the organisation has appropriately audited or reviewed financials, it must ensure that the financial statements are readily accessible and that they can be supplied to any legitimate requesting party.  This enables the organisation to comply with Standard 8.3, which requires that \'"the organisation must supply at any time a copy of its most recent audited\/reviewed financial statements to any legitimate stakeholder who submits a written request".\n\nLegitimate stakeholders include:\n - Organisation Members\n - Regulatory Bodies\n - Donors\n - NFP or NGO partner organisations\n - Staff and Volunteers\n - Creditors and Suppliers\n\nWe recommend the inclusion of summary financial statements information into your Annual Report, and that the annual report be itself uploaded to the ACNC Portal.  This maximised transparency and minimises the cost of addressing individual financial information requests.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 08:16:01',
