    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 6.1 requires the preparation of financial statements.  Standard 8.3 requires that \'"the organisation must supply at any time a copy of its most recent audited\/reviewed financial statements to any legitimate stakeholder who submits a written request".\n\nLegitimate stakeholders include:\n - Organisation Members\n - Regulatory Bodies\n - Donors\n - NFP or NGO partner organisations\n - Staff and Volunteers\n - Creditors and Suppliers\n\nThe organisation must, in addition to complying with Standard 6.1 (addressed elsewhere), ensure that the financial statements are readily accessible and that they can be supplied to any legitimate requesting party.  If the organisation has not been operating long enough to have yet generated financial reports, the Board should diarise a due date for the generation, review and finalisation of these reports in order to ensure they are ready in time to meet ACNC requirements.\n\nWe recommend the inclusion of summary financial statements information into your Annual Report, and that the annual report be itself uploaded to the ACNC Portal.  This maximised transparency and minimises the cost of addressing individual financial information requests.',
