    id: '1000',
    question_id: '230',
    order: '1',
    text: "We have never been asked for that kind of report from a donor or volunteer to a particular appeal; I'm not sure what our posture would be about that.",
    detailed: null,
    score: '2.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 8.4 requires that "the organisation must supply a summary report on the financial and operational results of any significant specific purpose appeal, in response to a written request from a donor to or volunteer of that project. The organisation may charge a reasonable fee reflecting the costs and effort of supplying the report".\n\nThe Board should define a mechanism for the receipt of such requests, how they will be processed (and by who), and what format the information will be supplied in.  This mechanism should also allow for how a suitable fee might be determined (advised to the requesting person in advance of the work being done).\n\nWe recommend that your annual report include as standard summary information on appeal outcomes in order to provide a ready reference point to satisfy the largest number of any queries you might receive.  Persons seeking more details that those published can then be reasonably charged for the work associated to researching, documenting and sending that extra information.',
