    text: "No, there are family members of the CEO who's remuneration has not been approved in writing by the Board.",
    detailed: null,
    score: '1.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '30',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Related to Standard 8.8, the CMA Standards Council\'s Policy for Excellence in Remuneration-Setting requires that "the Board approve the total remuneration package of any member of the CEO’s family who is employed by the organisation or any of its subsidiaries or related entities".\n\nThe Board should identify any and all members of the CEO\'s family so employed and review their total remuneration packages for propriety (ie that the remuneration is commensurate with the role and the individuals capability and experience profile).\n\nThe Board should be prepared to take action in the event that impropriety in setting remuneration is suspected or detected.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 08:55:49',
    updated_at: '2025-01-14 08:55:49',
