    id: '1108',
    question_id: '249',
    order: '1',
    text: "I'm not sure about every item having all of these data points.",
    detailed: null,
    score: '2.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 9.5 requires that "every item of communication used for solicitation of gifts must clearly identify the organisation\'s name, address, phone number, ABN (if applicable), and the purpose for which support is being solicited".\n\nThe Board should ensure that all written and persistent communication items (direct mail, email, brochures, posters, etc) clearly identify these data points.\n\nMore transient media such as social media does not typically support the real estate requirements to include all this data; we recommend (subject to comment from CMA -SC) that social media incorporate a URL either embedded in a post or pinned to the commentary on a post that links to a webpage that contains all these data points.  Radio ads should include a web URL verbalised in the content to allow listeners to find these details with ease.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 10:40:53',
    updated_at: '2025-01-14 10:40:53',
