    detailed: null,
    score: '2.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 9.6 requires that "the organisation must have a plan for how funds will be applied in the case of an appeal for a particular purpose being oversubscribed".\n\nIn these scenarios, option can include making donors aware that any oversubscriptions will be reallocated, eg to a secondary project or diverted to \'where most needed\', refunding a portion of each donation, refunding any donations received after the target was reached, etc.  \n\nPlanning for how funds will be applied in case of an oversubscribed appeal means your organisation can better respond to unexpected surpluses, allocate resources efficiently, and maintain their reputation.',
