    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Standard 9.6 requires that "the organisation must have a plan for how funds will be applied in the case of an appeal for a particular purpose being... undersubscribed".\n\nIn these scenarios, option can include making donors aware of what will happen if a donation cannot be utilised as intended.  Typical options would be that funds could be reallocated to a similar endeavour, diverted to \'where most needed\', added to general operational funds, or even refunded.  Alternately, keeping the campaign open for longer until targets are met is an option.\n\nPlanning for how funds will be applied in case of an undersubscribed appeal supports your financial stability, transparency, and helps maintain donor trust.',
    created_at: '2025-01-14 10:52:41',
    updated_at: '2025-01-14 10:52:41',
