    score: '2.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Every NFP of any organisation structure type must have a documented Constitution or a set of Rules that defines the purpose and operations of the organisation.  The Constitution \/ Rules define the rights and responsibilities of members and office holders, and - critically - comprise a contract between the association and its members.\n\nIf you do not have a Constitution or set of Rules - or if they have been lost in the transitions of time - (re)establishing such a document must be a major priority for the Board.\n\nThe type of document you need depends on your organisation type.  Most jurisdictions provide model rules or template constitutions for Incorporated Associations.  \n\nThe ACNC provides template constitutions for companies limited by guarantee and unincorporated associations that have charitable purpose.\n\nSee our Guide to Constitutions and Model Rules to find a set of rules that match your organisation type.',
