    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'A risk management policy benefits NFPs by enhancing decision-making, protecting assets and reputation, improving governance and compliance, building stakeholder confidence, enhancing organisational resilience, optimising resources, identifying opportunities, and promoting long-term sustainability.\n\nAll organisations should have a sound Risk Management Policy and associated procedure.\n\nIf the Board is unsure about the status of its Risk Management Policy, it should move to confirm such a policy exists and make it accessible, or move to adopt a new Policy.  Some states and territories provide model policies and useful additional artefacts to assist in your risk management endeavours.\n\nSee our Template: Risk Management Policy and Procedure for a helpful Risk Management Policy and procedure starting point.  This document also includes a link to a risk documentation template to support the procedure.',
