    action_text:
      "For organisation that engage volunteers, a Volunteer Management Policy serves as a foundational framework for engaging, supporting, and empowering volunteers, ultimately contributing to the overall success and impact of the organisation.\n\nAll organisations engaging volunteers should have a Volunteer Management Policy.\n\nThe Board should move to confirm such a policy exists and make it accessible, or move to adopt a new Policy. \n\nSee our Template: Volunteer Management Policy and Procedure for a helpful starting point. \n\nNote, while NFP members (including Board members) are technically volunteers, Members are subject to a different set of rights and responsibilities.  In a scenario where an organisation's only volunteers are Members who are not involved in service delivery, advocacy or other activities that involve interaction with external stakeholders, a Volunteer Management Policy is probably not required.",
