    action_text:
      'An IT governance framework provides a structured approach for NFPs to effectively manage and govern their IT resources, processes, and investments, enabling them to maximise value, minimise risks, and achieve their mission and objectives in a dynamic and evolving digital landscape.  \n\nIt is recommended that all organisations implement an IT Governance Framework.\n\nThe Board should consider adopt an IT Governance Framework. \n\nSee our Template: IT Governance Framework for a helpful starting point.  Larger NFPs with complex operations may wish to consider the ISACA (The Information and Systems Audit and Control Association) COBIT (Control Objectives in Information Technology) IT Governance framework.  This is a rich, advanced and well established framework; however, its implementation is considered beyond the scope of small-to-medium NFPs due to its depth and relative complexity.',
