    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'It is extremely important for NFPs to stay informed about evolving legal and regulatory requirements, as well as industry best practices, to ensure compliance with relevant standards and safeguard the privacy, security, and integrity of sensitive information entrusted to them by donors, volunteers, beneficiaries, and other stakeholders.  \n\nA number of public bodies work in this area to support individuals, families and organisations from external cyber threats.  We have developed a Template: Cybersecurity Policy and Procedures that draws on work of the Australian Cyber Security Centre https:\/\/www.cyber.gov.au\/ and the US National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) cyber security framework https:\/\/www.nist.gov\/cyberframework.\n\nOur framework is designed to suit NFPs who are unsure about, or in the early days, of establishing sound information management practices, and need to cover the basics quickly and efficiently.  Both ASCC and NIST offer comprehensive and extensive free resources that can be adopted for organisations with the capability and capacity to deepen their Information Security frameworks.\n\nNote, this assessment is designed to test the existence of an Information Security \/ Cybersecurity Framework; it does not (at this time) assess the validity,  maturity or suitability for purpose of that framework.  Organisations with an existing Information Security Framework are encouraged to assess their existing framework against our template to satisfy themselves that the basics of information security requirements are adequately satisfied.',
