    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Implementing a program evaluation process offers NFPs a range of benefits, including improved program effectiveness, informed decision-making, accountability, learning, fundraising opportunities, innovation, stakeholder engagement, and impact demonstration. By investing in evaluation, NFPs can strengthen their capacity to achieve meaningful and sustainable outcomes for the communities they serve.  \n\nIt is recommended that all organisations that run programs to external stakeholders implement a Program Evaluation Policy and Process.\n\nIf the Board is unsure about the status of its Program Evaluation Policy and Process, it should move to confirm such a document exists and make it accessible, or move to adopt a new one. \n\nSee our Template: Program Evaluation Policy and Process for a helpful starting point.',
