    action_text:
      'The ability to measure impact is an increasingly expected capability for NFPs as they create transparency, provide a basis for evidence-based decision making, and support scenarios where funding is based on outcomes, not transactions.  It is, in a sense, a comparative advantage for NFPs competing for funding.  It is also just good governance - it enables the Board to determine the degree to which the organisation is actually meeting its core purpose, and provides insights into how to improve the effectiveness - and consequential impact - of the organisation.\n\nThe Board should determine whether it has an Impact Assessment Policy and Framework, and if not, to consider implementing one.  See our Template: Impact Assessment Policy and Framework for a helpful guide.',
