      'Implementing a child safe policy is not only a legal (in most jurisdictions) and ethical obligation for NFPs but also a strategic investment in protecting children, enhancing organisational reputation, and fostering a culture of safety and accountability.  \n\nIf your organisation interacts with children or young people, or if your organisation operates in a jurisdiction where all NFPs are required to have one (New South Wales, Victoria, South Australia, Tasmania and Western Australia), the Board must ensure the creation and implementation of a Child Safe policy.\n\nSee our Template: Child Safety Policy and Procedures for a helpful starting point.  Note that child safety obligations vary by state and you may have obligations to multiple government bodies.  Our template represents a good starting point, but work will be required to customise the template to your locational, legal and operational circumstances.  The policy template contains guidance on how to do this.',
