    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Implementing a child safe policy is a legal obligation in many jurisdictions; moreover, it is an ethical one too for NFPs.  Such a policy represents a strategic investment in protecting children, enhancing organisational reputation, and fostering a culture of safety and accountability.  \n\nHaving a Child Safe policy is a mandatory legal requirement (as at February 2025) for all NFPs in New South Wales, Victoria, South Australia, Tasmania and Western Australia.  If you operate in any of these jurisdictions, the Board should ensure the creation and implementation of a Child Safe policy as a matter of compliance urgency.  Organisations not operating in those jurisdictions are also encouraged to plan for the creation of such a policy as good practice.\n\nSee our Template: Child Safety Policy and Procedures for a helpful starting point.  Note that child safety obligations vary by state and you may have obligations to multiple government bodies.  Our template represents a good starting point, but work will be required to customise the template to your locational, legal and operational circumstances.  The policy template contains guidance on how to do this.',
    created_at: '2025-02-09 07:11:27',
