    order: '2',
    text: 'Some\/most of our policies have a review date defined.',
    detailed: null,
    score: '5.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Policies can become outdated as laws, regulations, and best practices evolve. Regular reviews ensure that policies remain relevant, accurate, and in compliance with current standards and legal requirements.  A defined review date facilitates for regular assessment of the effectiveness of policies and the opportunity to make necessary adjustments to improve operations and governance.  It also holds the organisation accountable for regularly evaluating and updating its policies. This prevents policies from being neglected or forgotten over time and gives stakeholders confidence that the organization is proactive in maintaining effective and relevant policies.\n\nThe Board should define a review frequency for every policy, and determine a "next review date" for each policy.  The review frequency and next review date should be included in the body of each policy document.',
