      'Having a delegations document is important for your organisation in order to clearly defines the authority and decision-making powers delegated to specific individuals or positions within the organisation.  \n\nClearly defined delegations promote accountability, manage risks by specifying the limits of authority for different roles and functions within the organisation, clarifies the boundaries of authority within an organisation, and can help continuity of operations and governance, even during periods of transition or change in leadership.\n\nA delegations document is ultimately a legal instrument that allows Boards to delegate their legal responsibilities to the CEO and Executive Leadership in an accountable way.\n\nThe Board should move to develop a delegations instrument, using our Template: Organisational Delegations document as a guide.',
