    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Conducting regular board performance assessments is essential for promoting accountability, governance effectiveness, compliance, strategic alignment, and continuous improvement within not-for-profit organisations. By regularly evaluating and enhancing board performance, organisations can strengthen their capacity for achieving mission-driven impact and fulfilling their commitment to stakeholders.  \n\nRegular Board assessments will also help new Board members align with behavioural and compliance expectations sooner, maximising their contribution from the start. \n\nIt is recommended that the Board schedule annual Board assessments using GovernApp.  Our recommended timing is Q3 of your financial year.  This allows time to review the assessment outcomes, consolidate and update the generated GovernApp action plan, and report the fact of the assessment and the actions undertaken and planned to your Annual General Meeting.  This will maximise your accountability to members and ensure an ongoing focus on continuously improving Board governance.\n\nA review of the progress made against the GovernApp action plan should be a standing item on your Board meetings.\n\nAll new Board members should conduct a GovernApp self-assessment to help them get up to speed with governance concepts, language and expectations, and to identify areas where they need to come rapidly up to speed in order to maximise their Board contribution.',
