    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Investing in the professional development of board members is helpful for ensuring effective governance, strategic leadership, and organisational success within non-profit organisations. It fosters a culture of continuous learning, growth, and excellence that benefits the entire organisation and its stakeholders.  However, there are certain guidelines that need to be considered to ensure such development opportunities comply with legal requirements, uphold principles of good governance, be relevant to the Board member’s duties and responsibilities, and be financially prudent to undertake.\n\nWhile the organisation may not be able to financially support Board professional development activities now, if the organisation reaches a position where it can do so, it is recommended that you formally document your approach to this in order to to ensure the organisation meets its fiduciary obligations.  See our Model Practice: Board Training and Development as a starting point.',
