    score: '5.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "The goal of reviewing the register of interests is to promote transparency, integrity, and accountability in the organisation's governance practices. By conducting regular reviews, NFP boards can mitigate risks, uphold ethical standards, and maintain stakeholder trust and confidence in their leadership.\n\nIt is recommended that the Board schedule annual reviews of the register of interests.  In addition, the Board should consider the following events as potential triggers to an additional out-of-cycle review of the Register:\n\n - changes in board membership, \n - updates to relevant laws or regulations governing conflicts of interest\n - new partnerships: whenever the organisation initiates new  partnerships, review the register of interests to assess potential conflicts and ensure they are appropriately managed\n - whenever the organisation updates its policies or procedures related to conflicts of interest or governance transparency.",
    created_at: '2025-02-11 05:47:06',
