    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'NFP boards should ideally receive the agenda and associated papers well in advance of a meeting to allow board members sufficient time to review the materials thoroughly and prepare for discussions. However, unless the agenda is typically very complex, much earlier than two weeks in advance risks Boards receiving reports which are close to being out of date, especially with respect to operational updates, risks reports and current issues updates.\n\nThe Board should ensure that the (agreed) agenda and papers are regularly issued between one to two weeks in advance of any Board meetings, and enshrine this expectation in both the Governance Policy and the Secretary and CEO position descriptions.',
    created_at: '2025-02-18 01:59:52',
