    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'It is extremely helpful for board minutes to consistently and accurately reflect how decisions were arrived at and the reasoning behind those decisions; doing so increases transparency and accountability. If questions arise about a particular decision or the reasoning behind it, having documented evidence in the minutes can help clarify the decision-making process and the factors considered.\n\nIncluding the reasoning behind decisions enhances the historical value of the minutes and provides context for future board members and stakeholders. By understanding the factors considered and the rationale behind previous decisions, board members can make more informed choices in similar situations in the future.\n\nTo improve minute taking, the Board should consider adopting a defined minute taking practice, such as our Model Practice: Taking Effective Board Minutes.',
