    action_text:
      "The frequency with which Boards should review their delegations instrument depends on factors such as the organisation's size, complexity, operating environment, and the extent of changes in its governance structure or activities. However, as a general guideline, Boards should review their delegations instrument at least annually, and more frequently if significant changes occur. \n\nThe Board should consider ensuring a more regular frequency for reviewing its delegations instrument, with a bias towards adopting an annual review.  It is helpful to document this in your Template: Governance Policy.",
