    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '10',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Conflict among NFP board members negatively impacts the organisation by diverting attention from its mission and strategic goals, leading to inefficiency and reduced effectiveness in decision-making. \n\nIf there is an existing Board conflict resolution policy, the Board should commit to ensuring that it is applied in intra-Board conflict situations.  The Board may consider reviewing our  Template: Board Dispute Resolution Policy and Procedure to see if the current policy and process can be improved.  If no policy exists, the Board should adopt one, based on the above-mentioned template.\n\nThe Board may wish to analyse why conflict resolution processes are not being applied.  This may be driven by deeper issues that may in human reality overwhelm a paper policy. Typical causes of intra-Board conflict include divergent personalities and values, competition for leadership roles or influence within the board, lack of clear roles and responsibilities, disagreements over strategy and priorities, personal agendas, a lack of trust and respect, and influences from external stakeholders. The Board should reflect on these factors, possibly with the assistance of a skilled facilitator, and determine whether there are more strategic actions it could undertake to address underlying causes of intra-Board conflict.',
