    risk_id: '30',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "Your assessment results indicate that the Board does not have a good and shared understanding of balance sheets.\n\nA balance sheet, also known as a statement of financial position, is a financial statement that provides a snapshot of an organisation's financial condition at a specific point in time. It shows the assets, liabilities, and the net (balance) of these, calculated as follows:\n\nNet assets = Assets - Liabilities\n\nBalance sheets for NFPs have material differences to profit-making enterprises.  For more information on balance sheets, see our model practice.\n\nUnderstanding the balance sheet is a core skill for Board members.  The Board may also wish to consider acquiring training in reading and understanding financial statement for Boards.",
