    action_text:
      "Continuing to operate while insolvent is a serious issue, and can lead to civil and even criminal penalties.  To this end, the Board has a common duty to be aware of the financial health of the organisation, and must ensure that the organisation keeps adequate financial records to correctly record and explain the company’s transactions, its financial position and performance.\n\nAn organisation is insolvent when it is unable to pay its debts as they fall due. Note that it is of no consequence under law that assets exceed liabilities.\n\nBoards should ensure that a consideration of solvency is part of their review of the organisation's financial status, and that the minutes of Board meetings - or the AGM at the very least - also include a declaration of solvency.",
