    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'Your response suggests that the Board is unsure if it complies with the rules in its governing document relating to member accountability.\n\nTo ensure compliance with the rules in its governing document that deal with accountability to members, Board members and key staff should have a comprehensive understanding of the governing document, including all rules and procedures related to accountability.  The Board should review these rules in its constitution (or equivalent) and consider whether they are in fact complying with member accountability rules.\n\nThe Board should place strongest emphasis on:\n\n - Complying with the rules around holding Annual General Meetings (AGMs) as required, ensuring members are given adequate notice and the opportunity to attend, participate, and vote on key issues;\n - Maintaining accurate and up-to-date records of all decisions, communications, and financial transactions, which provide evidence to support accountability; and\n - Implementing a Conflict of Interest policy requiring board members and staff to disclose any potential conflicts of interest, and establish procedures for managing conflicts of interest to ensure decisions are made in the best interest of the charity and its members.',
    created_at: '2025-03-13 05:01:04',
