      "Charities have many ways to communicate with members about its activities, financial circumstances and any significant changes.  Your charity should consider any or all of the following:\n\n - Provide updates via the organisation's website and social media;\n - Produce an annual report for members which includes financial information and achievements towards the charity’s purposes;\n - Provide regular updates through newsletters, emails, and official communications, detailing the charity’s activities, financial status, and any significant decisions; and\n - Distribute minutes of meetings and financial reports to members promptly, ensuring transparency.",
