    action_text:
      'The AGM is a key accountability instrument for charities.   Your charity must hold an annual general meeting (AGM) that includes a ‘question and answer’ session.  There should be a documented process in place for members to propose resolutions and to vote on them at an AGM.\n\nThe ACNC provides several templates relating to AGM notices, agenda and minutes.  Note, the ACNC template Notice of AGM does not include guidance to members on how to propose resolutions or agenda items, we recommend that you add this to your AGM notices.',
