    action_text:
      'Your response suggests that the Board is unsure if the organisation allows its members to ask questions, vote on resolutions and raise concerns.\n\nThe AGM is a key accountability instrument for charities.   The Board must ensure that the charity holds an annual general meeting (AGM) that includes a ‘question and answer’ session every year.  There should be a documented process in place for members to propose resolutions and to vote on them at an AGM.\n\nThe ACNC provides several templates relating to AGM notices, agenda and minutes.  Note, the ACNC template Notice of AGM does not include guidance to members on how to propose resolutions or agenda items, we recommend that you add this to your AGM notices.',
