      "Your charity must having a clear processes for appointing Responsible People (such as board or committee members).  This process may be defined in your charity's governing document.  If not defined in your governing document, that document must contain a reference to where members can find and review that process.\n\nThe Board should proactively notify members when Board vacancies or new recruitment opportunities arise.  Ideally, each role on the Board (or associated committees) will ahve a position description, such as provided in the GovernApp Template: Board Roles and Responsibilities.\n\nNote, when appointing (or removing) Responsible People, you must must notify the ACNC via the ACNC Charity Portal.",
