    action_text:
      'Maintaining currency with Australian Law across local, State\/Territory and federal jurisdictions is onerous but required.  To ensure compliance with its regulatory obligations, your charity can adopt several practices to stay informed and up-to-date:\n\n - Regularly check the ACNC website for updates and subscribe to their newsletters to stay informed about federal requirements and changes in legislation;\n - Subscribe to updates from your relevant state or territory regulatory bodies;\n - Where necessary, engage legal professionals who specialise in charity law to provide advice and updates on regulatory changes.\n - Use accountants who understand the specific financial reporting and compliance requirements for charities, and provide proactive advice to their clients about changes that may cause impact\n - Join peak bodies and associations such as Volunteering Australia, Philanthropy Australia, or the Institute of Community Directors Australia (ICDA). These organisations often provide resources, training, and updates on regulatory changes.\n - Attend workshops and seminars and webinars focused on governance, compliance, and regulatory updates.\n - If your capacity and financial status permits, assign a specific individual, team or committee within the charity to monitor regulatory compliance and manage updates.\n - Regularly use compliance review software such as GovernApp to track regulatory requirements.',
    created_at: '2025-03-13 06:27:02',
    updated_at: '2025-03-13 06:27:02',
