    score: '0.00',
    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '30',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'The best way to ensure that your Responsible Persons remain suitable once appointed is to schedule regular (eg annual) reviews of the ASIC Banned and Disqualified Register for all your Responsible Persons.  Further, a register of National Police check and Working with Children check statuses should be maintained, so the Charity can require their Responsible Persons (as well as others to whom this applies) to renew these checks in a timely manner.\n\nIn this way the Charity can ensure its Responsible Persons, and those dealing with vulnerable people, remain suitable during their time of engagement with the Charity.\n\nSee the GovernApp Model Practice: Renewing Organisation Checks for ready guidance on how to implement this practice in your organisation.',
    created_at: '2025-03-13 08:10:43',
    updated_at: '2025-03-13 08:10:43',
