    action_text:
      'The ACNC summarises the general responsibilities of Responsible Persons for all Charities as follows:\n\n - "to act with reasonable care and diligence\n - to act honestly and fairly in the best interests of the charity and for its charitable purposes\n - not to misuse their position or information they gain as a Responsible Person\n - to disclose conflicts of interest\n - to ensure that the financial affairs of the charity are managed responsibly, and\n - not to allow the charity to operate while it is insolvent*."\n\nIn addition, Responsible Persons should have clarity around their specific obligations to the Charity they serve.  The Board should ensure that this is achieved through:\n\n - Providing the Responsible Person with a position description (or equivalent) that clearly states the the expectations of that Person in the specific role they are engaged in.  If your organisation lacks such position descriptions, see the GovernApp Template: Board Roles and Responsibilities document.\n - Providing the Responsible Person with a copy of the organisation\'s Code of Conduct \n - Providing the Responsible Person with a copy of the ACNC Governance for Good guide\n - Providing induction training for new Responsible Persons, including time with the Chair and the CEO\n - Defining a program of training for the Responsible Person to address any areas of development they have in relation to governance.\n\nWe recommend that all new Responsible Persons conduct a GovernApp self-assessment as an introduction to governance language and concepts.\n\n* https:\/\/www.acnc.gov.au\/tools\/factsheets\/responsible-people-board-or-committee-members',
    created_at: '2025-03-13 08:39:29',
    updated_at: '2025-03-13 08:42:55',
