      'Responsible Persons are responsible for monitoring the charity’s governance arrangements.  This includes the establishment and regular review of policies and procedures.\n\nCharities in Australia are required to develop a non-trivial number of mandatory policies, including (but not limited to):\n\n - Code of Conduct \/ Ethics\n - Financial Policies and Procedures\n - Conflict of interest\n - Privacy\n - Whistleblower\n - Health and Safety\n - Diversity and Inclusion\n - Risk Management\n - Records Management and retention\n\nThose interacting with young or other vulnerable people will also require child protection\/vulnerable persons policies and procedures.\n\nWe recommend that you conduct a Board assessment using the Four Frames assessment framework in GovernApp.  The Structural domain assesses you against all mandatory policies and procedures, and will provide you with template policies from its knowledgebank where you have identified gaps.',
