    is_triggering_action: '1',
    risk_id: '20',
    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      'If your Charity has been associated with past incidents of institutional child sexual abuse, it has a moral and ethical obligation to participate in the Redress Scheme.  Participation allows the charity to acknowledge past wrongs, provide support to survivors, and offer redress in the form of monetary payments, counseling, and a direct personal response.\n\nWhile participation is not legally mandatory, non-participation could have negative implications, especially if the charity is later found to have been involved in abuse cases that could have been addressed through the scheme.\n\nJoining the scheme provides a structured and government-supported way to support survivors of abuse. It ensures that survivors receive redress without having to go through the potentially re-traumatizing process of litigation.\n\nParticipation can be part of a broader risk management strategy. It can mitigate the risk of future claims or litigation, and it aligns the charity with national standards of care and responsibility towards survivors of institutional abuse.',
