    is_na: '0',
    action_text:
      "There are a number of circumstances that require your Charity to notify the ACNC of changes, being:\n\n - Changes to Responsible Persons\n - Changes to charity’s legal name\n - Changes to governing documents\n - Change in address for service\n - Changes to financial accounts.\n - Change in charity subtype\n - Winding up or dissolution\n - Change in charity cize affecting its size classification (small, medium, or large).\n - Serious incidents that may affect the charity’s operations or reputation.\n - Change in the charity’s legal status or activities that affect its eligibility for registration.\n - Change to the charity's ABN\n\nYour induction process should include an overview of these notification obligations.  Further, you should have a defined Responsible Person who is responsible for reporting these changes.  This responsibility should be embedded in their position description.",
